By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post)  –  The Abubakar Bukola Saraki Campaign Organization (ABSCO) has appointed Mr. Ilemona Onoja as spokesperson for the campaign.  The appointment which takes immediate effect was announced on Saturday in a statement signed by the Director General, Abubakar Bukola Saraki Campaign Organisation, Hon. Mohammed Wakil.  Mr. Onoja, a legal practitioner, was educated at the Benue State University, Makurdi. He attended the Nigerian Law School, Lagos campus and was called to the Nigerian Bar in 2006. Over the years, Onoja has been a very vocal voice in the campaign for good governance, respect for human rights and upholding the principles of the rule of law. 